-- Mondi Rallies to Six-Month High After Saying 2011 Profit Rose
-- B y   J a n i c e   K e w
-- 2012-02-14T09:34:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/mondi-rallies-to-six-month-high-after-saying-2011-profit-rose.html
Mondi Group (MND) ,  Europe ’s largest maker
of office paper, rose to the highest in six months after saying
its underlying operating profit in 2011 was “considerably
higher” than that of a year earlier.  The shares advanced as much as 4.3 percent to 67.82 rand
and traded at 67.68 rand at 10:48 a.m. in Johannesburg, heading
for its highest close since July 27.  Earnings per share excluding one-time items rose to between
67 euro cents to 72 cents, compared with 47 cents a year
earlier, Johannesburg-based Mondi said in a statement today.  The median estimate of 12 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg is
for adjusted earnings per share of 66 euro cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Janice Kew in Johannesburg at 
